The Senator representing Lagos Central Senatorial District, Senator Oluremi Tinubu has urged women to rise up and equip themselves to fill gaps in politics, public office, and management. Speaking against the backdrop of the International Women’s Day, Tinubu said this can only be done if all women are ready to make a difference, speak up for worthy causes and impact on their immediate communities, ‘the type of change they wish to see.’ While assuring women of her unwavering commitment to the empowerment of Nigerian Women, she noted that men have a role to play in order to adequately entrench the rights of women, abrogate gender-based violence and ensure equal opportunities for all. A look at the Senate’s women Tinubu planning to be president through backdoor - Fani-Kayode Is Tinubu the problem with Nigeria?